name: WHSmith
summary: WH Smith, a historic British retailer, is reportedly in discussions to sell its high street business, which includes over 500 stores. The company, which has been operating for over 230 years, is considering the move as part of a strategic review. The potential sale could involve all of WH Smith's high street operations, including bookstores, newsagents, and post offices, and would impact approximately 5,000 employees. The news has caused speculation about the future of the company's physical presence on British high streets, which have faced significant challenges in recent years.

summary: Arsenal secured a crucial 1-0 victory against Wolverhampton Wanderers (Wolves) in the Premier League. name: Omar Marmoush
summary: Manchester City have completed the signing of Omar Marmoush from Eintracht Frankfurt for a reported fee of £59 million. The 23-year-old Egyptian forward has signed a long-term contract with the Premier League champions. Marmoush has been in impressive form for Frankfurt this season, scoring seven goals in 19 appearances in all competitions. He was also part of the Egypt squad that won the Africa Cup of Nations in 2022. City have been keen to add to their attacking options and Marmoush is seen as a player with great potential. He is expected to compete with the likes of Erling Haaland, Julian Alvarez and Riyad Mahrez for a place in the team.

name: Kyle Walker
summary: Kyle Walker, the Manchester City captain, is set to join AC Milan on loan for the remainder of the season. Manchester City has accepted AC Milan's offer for the England international, and the transfer has been officially confirmed. Walker is expected to arrive in Italy on Tuesday to complete the move, which will last for two and a half years. The loan deal is part of Manchester City's plan to reduce their squad size ahead of the summer transfer window. Walker has been with Manchester City since 2017, winning four Premier League titles and an FA Cup. He has made 233 appearances for the club in all competitions. Walker's departure from Manchester City has led to speculation that the club may be interested in signing AC Milan's left-back, Theo Hernandez. However, Manchester City has not yet made an offer for Hernandez.

summary: Manchester United and Chelsea are reportedly considering a player exchange deal involving Alejandro Garnacho and Christopher Nkunku. The potential swap deal has raised concerns about Garnacho's future at United, with some reports suggesting he could leave if Nkunku joins the club. United manager Erik ten Hag is reportedly keen on adding Nkunku to his squad but is said to be "lost for words" over the potential transfer failure. Meanwhile, Nkunku has reportedly made a decision on his future, but the details remain unclear. In a recent interview, Nkunku expressed his preference for playing in a central position on the pitch, suggesting that he may not be interested in a wide role at United if he were to join the club.
